<br>
Add the parameter: Popup = False<br>
-----------------<br>
Popup Parameter<br>
-----------------<br>
Boolean (True/False) Should the window popup immediately on page load or wait for your command to popup. You can popup or close a CFPowerWINDOW by with an event statement:<br>
<br>
To POPUP a non-displayed CFPowerWINDOW:<br>
<br>
OnClick = "cfpw_popup('WindowName')"<br>
<br>
To CLOSE a CFPowerWINDOW:<br>
<br>
OnClick = "cfpw_close('WindowName')"<br>
<br>
The cfpw_popup() and cfpw_close() commands call a javascript function within the tag, so they can be used just like calling any javascript function. REMEMBER: THEY ARE CASE-SENSITIVE commands. <br>
<br>
